<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0172 </DOCNO><TEXT>After outlining the fundamentals of explosion protection and the zoningof dangerous areas, the book presents regulations and specificationsfor the fabrication and use of electrical equipment in mines. The variousaspects of explosion-proof electrical equipment are considered, includingtesting and selection. The book is supplemented by 83 pictures, 24 tables,and many practical examples; it is recommended for manufacturers andusers of electrical equipment, practical engineers, teachers and studentsat universities.</TEXT></DOC>